 {"id":"bd-mei5","title":"resolver: execute resolver.json fixture family through harness matrix","description":"Concrete gap: crates/frankenlibc-harness/tests/resolver_conformance_test.rs only validates schema/coverage today, even though crates/frankenlibc_conformance/src/lib.rs already implements executable resolver fixture cases (ResolverConfig::default/parse, DnsHeader::new_query, encode_domain_name, lookup_hosts, getaddrinfo, gethostbyname). Add end-to-end execution of tests/conformance/fixtures/resolver.json through the harness subprocess in strict/hardened as applicable, compare impl_output to fixture expected_output, and fix any resolver host-contract mismatches the new execution test exposes.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T03:54:37.785083271Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T03:57:17.834958419Z","closed_at":"2026-04-21T03:57:17.832927706Z","close_reason":"Added harness-matrix execution for resolver.json and verified fixture outputs locally and via rch","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
